0 - The server has two routes:

/stat => requests server statistics.

/api => according to the query string, sends it to one of the two servers.

If id=abc then proxy to the server located at localhost:3000

If id=cde then proxy to the server located at localhost:3100

1 - To install, do:

npm install

2 - To activate the server:

npm start

3- To test

a) Start the already provided tiny-serverS on ports 3000 and 3100.
   Create two windows and do:
      i) on window1: npm start -- 3000
     ii) on window2: npm start -- 3100

b) start this server:
   npm start (or node app.js OR ./app.js  if in a UNIX machine), which will
   start listening on port 4000

c) on a browser (firefox will be better for the expected json responses) do:

http://localhost:4000/api?id=abc&a=10&b=20 <= will send the request to the server running on port 3000

http://localhost:4000/api?id=cde <= will send the request to the server running on port 3100

http://localhost:4000/stat <= will display the server statistics

4 - WARNING: We have explicitly decided not to handle any errors that may occur, nor do we use any logging system;
             THIS IS JUST A SKELETON of a reverse proxy.
